Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated creatinine, indicating impaired renal function, and markedly increased total bilirubin, suggesting possible liver dysfunction or hemolysis. There is metabolic acidosis (low arterial pH), mild hyperchloremia, and proteinuria with glucosuria, which may reflect renal tubular dysfunction or diabetes. Platelets are mildly elevated. HDL cholesterol is low, increasing cardiovascular risk. Other parameters are within normal limits. Clinical correlation and further evaluation of renal and hepatic status are recommended.
